ul.li: Achieve LDL cholesterol below 1.8 mmol/L to reduce cardiovascular risk.
Achieve total cholesterol below 4.0 mmol/L.
Achieve triglycerides below 1.7 mmol/L.
Maintain HDL cholesterol above 1.0 mmol/L.
Maintain blood pressure below 130/80 mmHg through lifestyle modifications.
Limit daily sodium intake to less than 2.3 grams to support blood pressure control.
Engage in at least 150 minutes of moderate-intensity aerobic physical activity per week.
Achieve at least 5% reduction in body weight if overweight or obese.
Patient will participate in diabetes self-management education to improve understanding and management of prediabetes and diabetes.
Achieve and maintain HbA1c at individualized target level.
Achieve and maintain fasting plasma glucose within recommended range.
Achieve weight reduction of at least 5% from baseline to improve glycemic control.
Achieve and maintain blood pressure within recommended range for diabetes.
